727834f-c.text:
Queens Boulevard, north side, east from 54th Street. In the foreground of views one and three is a section of the First Presbyterian Cemetery of Newtown. The three views also show an old structure that has since been modernized and is distinguishable by its dormmer windows. The homes seen in there order were the property of H. Geisling, 9.B,
Mrs. Raymond,and Rapelye in 1873.

1923
View 2: March 1923
View 3: July 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
